pr_body:
## Purpose

Add `RunOnceEx` functionality for ReactOS.
    
Final results for GSoC 2021 iernonce.

JIRA issue: [CORE-7194](https://jira.reactos.org/browse/CORE-7194)

## Work done

- Read the data from the registry.
- Show a dialog displaying items, and execute entries in section by alphabetical order, with an arrow indicating which one is executing.
- Add code for explorer to check & launch `rundll32.exe` for handling `RunOnceEx` registry when user logon.
- Implement `InitCallback` for registering callback functions receiving notifications after each entry is executed.
- Add `iernonce_undoc.h`

## Syntax & usage

`RunOnceEx` key is under `\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnceEx` of `HKLM` or `HKCU`.

The `Title` value with type `REG_SZ` represents the title of the dialog (can be absent)

The `Flags` value with type `REG_DWORD` represents the settings you want to use, can be one of the following values:
| Value | Function | Function definition |
| ----- | -------- | ------------------- |
| 0x00000000 | Default | All functions are disabled |
| 0x00000080 | No Status Dialog | Status dialog box is not displayed while `RunOnceEx` runs |

It can have multiple subkeys, each represents a section. Sections will be executed in alphabetical order.

For each section, it can have multiple values with type `REG_SZ`, representing commands. They will be executed in alphabetical order too.

The default value specifies the title of the section. If absent, this section won't be shown in the dialog but will still be carried out. 

`RunOnceEx` will be automatically performed when user logon, both `HKLM` and `HKCU` will only be performed when `HKLM` one is non-empty.

To manually run `RunOnceEx`, use the following command:
```
rundll32 iernonce.dll RunOnceExProcess
```

following is a simple example for `RunOnceEx`:
```
Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnceEx]
"Title"="Setup Title"

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnceEx\0001]
@="Notepad"
"RunNotepad"="notepad.exe"

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnceEx\0002]
@="calc and mspaint"
"bbb"="mspaint.exe"
"aaa"="calc.exe"
```

it will launch notepad, calc, and mspaint in order.

*note: the behavior of RunOnceEx on Win2k3 might be slightly different from the Win10 ones.*

## TODO for post-GSoC

- Add API test for `RunOnceExProcess` and `InitCallback`.
- Investigate `runonce.exe` in Windows.
